[試題] 101上 陳峙維 臺灣音樂導論 期中考











標題[試題] 101上 陳峙維 臺灣音樂導論 期中考

作者

gilthoniel22

                (乃菉)
            
            


看板

NTU-Exam



時間

                    2012-11-15 11:24:42
            








課程名稱︰臺灣音樂導論
課程性質︰臺灣研究學程、亞洲藝術學程、通識A13*
課程教師︰陳峙維
開課學院：文學院
開課系所︰音樂學研究所
考試日期（年月日）︰2012.11.14
考試時限（分鐘）：三個小時以內
是否需發放獎勵金：是
（如未明確表示，則不予發放）

試題 :

共有三十題選擇題，前十五題是聽力，後十五題是上課內容。


LISTENING: You will hear 15 musical examples in this section. Choose the






           best answer.


Example1

1. To which category of does this example belong?

   (A)Theatrical work(xiqu)戲曲             (B)Delicate song(youqu)幼曲

   (C)String score(xianpu)弦譜              (D)Instrumental suite(pu)譜


Example2

2. To what aboriginal people does this example belong; which of the following

   characteristics can you find?

   (A)Atayal;drone                          (B)Tsou;triadic harmony

   (C)Yami;canon                            (C)Bunun;triadic harmony


Example3

3. To which category does this piece belong?

   (A)Song suites(zhi)指                    (B)Instrumental suite(pu)譜

   (C)Individual songs(qu)曲                (D)Labelled tune(paizi)牌子


Example4

4. To what aboriginal people does this example belong; which of the following

   characteristics can you find in this example?

   (A)Rukai;drone                           (B)Amis;call-and-response

   (C)Amis;multi-part counterpoint          (D)Atayal; canon


Example5

5. Which of the following statemens about this piece is NOT correct?

   (A)The place name Kinmen is mentioned in this song.

   (B)The recording example is sung by Kimbo 胡德夫.

   (C)It features traditional musical idioms of the aboriginal people the

      composer belongs to.

   (D)It was composed during the Japanese colonial period.


Example6

6. Which of the following is NOT featured in this example?

   (A)The high-pitched male voice.          (B)Western harmony.

   (C)Traditional Puyuma musical uduioms.   (D)The style of choral singing.


Example7

7. To which aboriginal people does this example belong, what musical texture

   is it?

   (A)Atayal;monophonic                     (B)Amis;monophonic

   (C)Amis;polyphonic                       (D)Atayal;canonic


Example8

8. To what aboriginal people does this example belong?

   (A)Yami                                  (B)Truku

   (C)Puyuma                                (D)Paiwan


Example9

9. This example is

   (A)sung by Moutain Grandma.              (B)an ode to an Amis village.

   (C)a song dedicated to the composer's wife.(D)an adaption of a Bunun tune.


Example10

10. To which category of does this example belong?

    (A)Tgeatrical work(xiqu)曲              (B)Delicate song(youqu)幼曲

    (B)String score(xianpu)弦譜             (D)Labelled tune(paizi)牌子


Example11

11. To which category does this example belong?

    (A)Song suites(zhi)指                   (B)Instrumental suite(pu)譜

    (C)Individual songs(qu)曲               (D)Theatrical work(xiqu)戲曲


Example12

12. Which of the following statements about this piece is correct?

    (A)Its style is influenced by songs taught at schools during the Japanese

       colonial period.

    (B)It features the use of both the composer's mother tongue and Japanese

       in the lyrics.

    (C)It was composed during '823 Artillery Bombardment' in 1958.

    (D)It features the dotted rhythm commonly heard in music of aborigines in

       Taiwan.


Example13

13. To which category does this example belong?

    (A)Theatrical work(xiqu)戲曲            (B)Instrumental suite(pu)譜

    (C)Song suites(zhi)指                   (D)Individual songs(qu)曲


Example14

14. To which category does this example belong?

    (A)Theatrical work(xiqu)戲曲            (B)Labelled tune(paizi)牌子

    (B)String score(xianpu)弦譜             (D)Delicate song(youqu)幼曲


Example15

15. On what occasion and by what people would this kind of singing be

    performed?

    (A)At the monkey festival by the Pyuma.

    (B)After an initiation rite by the Amis.

    (C)At a wedding ceremony by the Rukai.

    (D)After a successful animal hunt by the Bunun.


MULTIPLE CHOICE: Choose the best answer(2 pts each question).


16. Which of the following statements about nanguan is NOT correct?

    (A)Nanguan has been widespread among the southern Fujianese diaspora.

    (B)Nanguan used to ne transmitted by amateur music clubs.

    (C)Taiwan's state intervention in nanguan has succeeded in transmitting

       the artistry of this important cultural heritage.

    (D)Nanguan clubs are often associated with temples which provide a palce

       for rehearsals in exchange for a club's servings during temple festivals.


17. Drum poetry 鼓詩 in beiguam

    (A)is written onto a musical staff with square notes.

    (B)is similar to sol-fa,but it only records the melodic skeleton.

    (C)uses onomatopoeic syllables representing different sound combination

       of percussion instruments.

    (D)is a series of Xs and Os representing when to hit each part of the drum

       kit.


18. Which of the following statements about aboriginal music and culture is

    correct?

    (A)Some scholars consider Taiwan aborigines the origin of Austronesian

       peoples.

    (B)Taiwan aboriginal music is mainly singing and is used only in rituals.

    (C)Both (A) and (B).

    (D)Neither (A) nor (B).


19. Which of the following statements about nanguan instruments is correct?

    (A)Pipa is held vertically.

    (B)Paiban consists of five pieces of wooden slabs.

    (C)When playing 'ten instruments altogether'十音會奏, the souna of beiguan

       is used to create the festive atmosphere.

    (D)Pipa is played with a plectrum.


20. Nanguan notatiotn

    (A)consists of at least three elements: pitch, meter and finger techniques.

    (B)only notates the dongxiao melody.

    (C)uses onomatopoeic syllables to record instructions for percussion

       instruments.

    (D)uses numbers to represent the skeleton melody.


21. Which of the following statements about the instruments of aborigines in

    Taiwan is NOT correct?

    (A)Traditionally aborigines in Taiwan seldom use loud instruments such as

       drums or gongs.

    (B)The Paiwan is famous for their double nose-flutes.

    (C)Musical bow is an important instrument among the Bunun.

    (D)Jew's harps are only found among the Atayal.


22. Which nanguan club's 1982 concert tour in Europe was so successful that it

    helped promote the privileged position of nanguan for gaining governmental

    support?

    (A)Gan-a-tsui江之翠.                    (B)Hantang Yuefu漢唐樂府.

    (C)Tainan Nanshengshe南聲社.            (D)Lugang Juyingshe聚英社.


23. The 'backstage' of beiguan theatre

    (A)is led by the coconut-box fiddle.

    (B)is also employed in Pear Garden drama.

    (C)accounts for 30% of a successful performance, according to a Taiwanese

       saying.

    (D)is led by the single-head drum player.


24. Which of the following statements about aboriginal musical changes is NOT

    correct?

    (A)The mid-1990s saw the rise of aboriginal sonsciousness and a boom of

       aboriginal fusion.

    (B)Taiwan aborigines did not learn to sing church hymns until the late

       Qing dynasty.

    (C)Singing was part of education at Common school for aboriginal childern

       蕃人公學校.

    (D)One of the major features of the aboriginal fusion is the adding of

       instrumental accompaniment to singing.


25. In Pear Garden drama (liyunxi) 梨園戲

    (A)the musical contents are based on beiguan.

    (B)the leader fo the accompanying ensemble is pipa.

    (C)the actors imitate the movement fo hand puppets.

    (D)the player of Southern drum (nangu)南鼓 place one foot on the drum and

       produces different pitches and timbres.


26. The string score (xianpu)弦譜 in beiguan

    (A)features a souna.

    (B)features a solo singer accompanied by a 'percussion and wind ensembles'.

    (C)is delivered by a 'silk and bamboo ensemble'.

    (D)is performed by a solo singer who leads the ensemble and maintains the

       beat with a clapper.


27. The 'Return to Innocence' incident

    (A)raised more attention from the general public in Taiwan to singers of

       aboriginal backgrounds.

    (B)resulted in a lawsuit which is still in progress.

    (C)was caused by an unauthorised sampling of Puyuma singing in an

       electronic music project.

    (D)led Difang and his wife to perform in the openinf ceremony of the

       Olympic Games.


28. Which of the following statements about the song 'Ocean'海洋 by Purder is

    correct?

    (A)The Mandarin Chinese pronunciation of the word Ocean 海洋 haiyang

       sounds similar to the vocables often be heard in the songs of the Bunun.

    (B)Purder was awarded 'Best Male Singer' in 2000 Golden Melody Awards for

       the album which this song is from.

    (C)Both (A) and (B).

    (D)Neither (A) nor (B).


29. Which of the following statements about beiguan is NOT correct?

    (A)The percussion-melodic insertion in 'labelled tunes' can be repeated as

       many times as necessary.

    (B)Beiguan can also be employed in the backstage ensembles of many theatres,

       such as string puppetry and hand puppetry.

    (C)Beiguan was originally popular in the regions north to Fujian and

       brought to Taiwan by immigrants.

    (D)Beiguan is one of the dominant traditional music genres brought by the

       immigrants from Fujian and thus the Fijianese dialect is used when

       performing vocal pieces.


30. Which statement about the presentation form 'array'排場 in beiguan is

    correct?

    (A)All forms of musical contents may be performed on this occasion.

    (B)Performers may sing without makeup, costume and acting.

    (C)Both (A) and (B).

    (D)Neither (A) nor (B).



ANSWERS:

1  BDBAD

6  CCABC

11 AADBD

16 CCABA

21 DCDBD

26 CABDC

